  "texts": [
    "GANs provide a significant contribution to the domain of biomedical imagery for image segmentation tasks.",
    "It has been utilized for the segmentation of tumors, pathology, and lesions from different body parts like the brain or liver, etc.",
    "GANs use segmented masks with input images to generate synthetic images with the segmentation of the target masks.",
    "Sometimes, during the training of GANs, the segmented masks are difficult to learn and GANs generate poorly segmented synthetic images or low-quality images.",
    "The literature Yi et al. (2019), Nalepa et al. (2019), Román et al. (2020), Iqbal et al. (2022) can be explored for more discussion on biomedical image segmentation."
  ],
